Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.26,0:00:02.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The distance between two\Npeople's love and hate
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.30,0:00:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two people's deduction\Nand suspense
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.97,0:00:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A surprise trick in a\Nquestionable apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.67,0:00:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sees through the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.37,0:00:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a child in appearance\Nwith the I.Q. of an adult
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.44,0:00:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No case is left unsolved with Detective Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.01,0:01:52.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We met a grandpa at Araide Clinic and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.77,0:01:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,heard a bizarre ghost story from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.88,0:01:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we came to his\Nsmall old apartment house which
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.61,0:02:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he said was haunted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.62,0:02:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, there is a building next\Nto his apartment house
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.22,0:02:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The builder had committed suicide\Nafter the bursting of the financial bubble.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.59,0:02:13.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a park in front of\Nhis apartment house too,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.53,0:02:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,where the burned body of\Na young woman was previously found.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.73,0:02:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place has many eerie stories\Nsurrounding it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.63,0:02:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and we fell asleep while\Nwaiting in grandfather's room
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.57,0:02:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,for the ghost to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.88,0:02:32.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get out of here...Get out of here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.08,0:02:38.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get out of here
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.35,0:02:40.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.59,0:02:45.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The toilet water turned red
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.96,0:02:46.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A spooky figure looks in through\Nthe window from outside
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.70,0:02:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sped \« figure looks in through\Nthe window from outside
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.30,0:02:50.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.50,0:02:52.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a supernatural fiery ball
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.60,0:02:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,IS said to appear in the building next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.54,0:03:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does this mean anyhow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.34,0:03:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ghost appearing on the TV screen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:05.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after suddenly fainting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.48,0:03:08.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The toilet water suddenly turning red.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.68,0:03:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both can be explained scientifically
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.59,0:03:15.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but what about the other two phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.93,0:03:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the death candle\Nand the figure in the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.49,0:03:20.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just can't seem to figure them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.86,0:03:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did the culprit do them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.73,0:03:28.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there a culprit in the! first places
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.14,0:03:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If one did exist
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.94,0:03:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.47,0:03:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And for what purpose\NIS the culprit doing all this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Truth of the Haunted House (Part ll)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.76,0:03:51.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.96,0:03:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you looking\Nat with the window open?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.43,0:03:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bugs will come flying in again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.70,0:03:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm wondering just about where that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.17,0:04:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,gramps saw the death candle in\Nthat building.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.14,0:04:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The spot where I saw it is in the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:08.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,around the center of that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.11,0:04:12.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The red light alone was looming and\Nmoving about in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.12,0:04:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At times it turned a bluish white light.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.25,0:04:20.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't believe me, go ask\NHouichi Otonashi\NI ll') u\N6 META
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.86,0:04:23.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Yotsuya of Room #2 and\NMr. Bancho of Room #4.\NHouichi Otonashi\N5 WMMmMEA
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.33,0:04:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each of them said that\Nthey once also saw the death candle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.40,0:04:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. yeah, I saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.47,0:04:33.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A red one and blue death candle as w\NIwahisa Yotsuya\NNe B22)\N2 LoASM¢N AN\NQQIEA
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.03,0:04:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when I visited the room\Nwhere my senior at school was livin\NIwahisa Yotsuya\Nma AM (22)\NCILIA\NSCHEME A
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.87,0:04:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your senior?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.97,0:04:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.94,0:04:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.61,0:04:42.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the room right above this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.54,0:04:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Room #6 is where my senior was living.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.42,0:04:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since then,\Nhe was unable to sleep properly
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.89,0:04:53.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because he was seized with\Nfear of the death candles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.59,0:04:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He finally moved out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:04:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was unable to sleep either,\Nnot because of fright,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.26,0:04:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but rather. because of being overexcited.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.56,0:05:01.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.90,0:05:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. this is a 8mm movie projector. right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.00,0:05:10.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm now using it to edit a movie filmed\Nby our film club in college.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.54,0:05:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this room is bloody awful,\Nfull of sick horror magazines and posters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.44,0:05:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.71,0:05:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel I'm going to have nightmares\Njust being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.95,0:05:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still. all this is nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.28,0:05:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,compared to\NRoom #4 where Mr.Bancho lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.55,0:05:27.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.49,0:05:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this room is really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.13,0:05:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There're tons of the\Nghost and monster figures here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.76,0:05:35.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kikuji Banhou\N&% BY 3% Xx (34)\N4§I&A
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.03,0:05:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You haven't seen anything yet.\NKikuji Banhou\NFE BI BT Xx (34)\NCS LQUOQL.\NAB EEA
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.77,0:05:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kikuji Banhou\NFE BY 5 Xx (34)\NaiiéA
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.27,0:05:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I turn the light off like so\NKikuji Banhou\NZE BY [ ox (34)\NAMET A
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.47,0:05:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I turn the light off like so
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.60,0:05:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yipes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.21,0:05:46.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1. The figures...\Nare glowing various colors in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.27,0:05:49.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because of this black light.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.41,0:05:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The special kind of fluorescent\Ncoating painted on the figures
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.15,0:05:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,reacts to black light making them\Nglow like a neon tube.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.28,0:05:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm...You know a lot, sonny.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.65,0:06:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A toy store owner told me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.19,0:06:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way,\Nyou also saw the death candle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.13,0:06:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I did
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.26,0:06:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but'l saw it through that window
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.36,0:06:08.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,not the window facing that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.60,0:06:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This window is located diagonally
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.80,0:06:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,below the window where\Nthe figure appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.14,0:06:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.47,0:06:20.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think you better close the window now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.61,0:06:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do it for our sister's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.08,0:06:26.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, in fact,\Na couple of moths have already entered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.55,0:06:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't believe\Nthe ghost story I told you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.75,0:06:34.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you better go talk with Botan of Room #1.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.86,0:06:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That-square grad student\Nwith a square head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.49,0:06:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.76,0:06:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've never seen it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.40,0:06:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe nothing but\Nwhat I can comprehend scientifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.27,0:06:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuyuhiko Botan
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.50,0:06:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuyuhiko Botan\NHR RE QR)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.77,0:06:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you know\Nwhat I hate more than that now?\NTsuyuhiko Botan\NHF mE (27)\N<LI.\NTS EREA
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.33,0:06:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuyuhiko Botan\NHA BE (27)\NkL} {IN
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.64,0:06:51.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That building opposite here\Nthat is still half done.\NTsuyuhiko Botan\NHER REED
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.51,0:06:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That building opposite here\Nthat is still half done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.04,0:06:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.51,0:06:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, sO. get a load of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.98,0:06:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That goddamn building\Nshuts out the sunlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.81,0:07:01.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the sun rarely shines into the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.25,0:07:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's certainly true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.39,0:07:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr.Otonashi's room diagonally\Nabove is much better than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.86,0:07:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it has a window\Nfacing the street side.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.29,0:07:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So. why don't you move out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.06,0:07:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the rent is so cheap and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.66,0:07:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,my grandma told me that\Nthis place had good feng shun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.40,0:07:22.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you say you believe only what\Nyou can comprehend scientifically, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.70,0:07:26.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. May I.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.14,0:07:27.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Smoke here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.98,0:07:29.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sure, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But please leave\Nafter you finish smoking the cigarette.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.91,0:07:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.78,0:07:34.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cigarette?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.18,0:07:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah".<... Ahh
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.05,0:07:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D...Dad.... your arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.99,0:07:42.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A moth again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.19,0:07:45.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Darn! Why always me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.13,0:07:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get them out of the room quickly! Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.90,0:07:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm trying to do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.24,0:08:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.71,0:08:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprits were afraid that the murder\Nthey committed would be revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.32,0:08:11.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they tried to destroy\Nthe decisive evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.29,0:08:14.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of/the woman that\Nthey burned to death 4 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.42,0:08:17.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They used ghosts\Nto cover up the evildoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.66,0:08:22.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?Are you leaving already?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.73,0:08:24.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The night's still young
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.33,0:08:27.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You may be missing out on seeing\None of the eeriest ghosts
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.30,0:08:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you've ever seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.67,0:08:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too bad you're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.87,0:08:32.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it'spperfectly all right with me\NIf you leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.91,0:08:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way I can get on with my paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.28,0:08:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,buddy,\Ntake it easy. say hello to the ghost for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.75,0:08:40.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heigh-ho.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.15,0:08:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How unsociable they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.42,0:08:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Faugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.09,0:08:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haunted by the ghost. my eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.25,0:08:48.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Making such a big fuss over illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.66,0:08:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm.? Where is Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.83,0:08:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. there he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.63,0:08:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! We're going home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.36,0:08:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got to go pee. but
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.30,0:08:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a bit scared to go alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.80,0:09:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. pops. please go with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.20,0:09:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.97,0:09:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.91,0:09:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on , why should I?\NAll right, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.94,0:09:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting outside then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.08,0:09:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Phew.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.35,0:09:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I've seen him somewhere before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.16,0:09:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.50,0:09:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Sonny!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.33,0:09:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you went home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.33,0:09:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've got trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.00,0:09:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.34,0:09:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ook. That restroom is cursed\NNo doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.41,0:09:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's so stinky and I can't flush the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.14,0:09:43.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.68,0:09:47.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it sure smells. but
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.75,0:09:52.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There seems no problem with flushing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.39,0:09:59.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wa-water is... Water is turning red
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.79,0:10:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tha-that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.76,0:10:02.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be true!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. boy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.90,0:10:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, the TV in your room is cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.74,0:10:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.57,0:10:09.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look. over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.14,0:10:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get out of here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.61,0:10:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ghost! That's the ghost!\NWhat should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.08,0:10:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This can't be happening
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.22,0:10:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing?\NThere is no tape inside
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.19,0:10:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.12,0:10:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.81,0:10:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,WwW. What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.38,0:10:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! So it appeared again! The ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.35,0:10:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. no way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.55,0:10:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There must be something wrong here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.92,0:10:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because everything was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.55,0:11:00.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.99,0:11:05.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were all tricks to\Nmake it look like the works of the ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.46,0:11:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying that nobody\Nbut you could have set the tricks up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.86,0:11:14.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because you created them. isn't that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:15.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bancho?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.94,0:11:19.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tricks.\NHow can you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.41,0:11:22.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man. you're acting like\Na detective or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.01,0:11:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,De-detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.81,0:11:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me\Nyou are the renowned detective
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.71,0:11:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sleeping Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.28,0:11:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.22,0:11:32.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I'm gonna unlock
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.42,0:11:37.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the mysteries of\Na lot of psychic phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.89,0:11:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First of all,\Nabout the toilet water turning red.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I noticed about it was that,\Nwhen I entered the restroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.23,0:11:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it smelled awfully of ammonia, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.97,0:11:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that the toilet{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} tan{\r}k\Nsmelled faintly of alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.64,0:11:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ammonia and alcohol?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.71,0:11:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.41,0:11:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you did an experiment in
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.25,0:12:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,science in your elementary school days,\Ndidn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.68,0:12:04.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you add one drop of\Nalkaline ammonia water to the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.39,0:12:08.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,colorless phenolphthalein\Nsolution dissolved in alcohol,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.29,0:12:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the red color will appear like magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.39,0:12:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.86,0:12:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but,\NI wonder if it would work out that well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.83,0:12:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The color in the experiment isn't\Nbright red but pinkish red.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.30,0:12:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The color could never be mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.30,0:12:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.57,0:12:27.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it would look like blood\Nin a dimly-lit restroom like here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.44,0:12:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well. even so
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.71,0:12:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there is no chemical reaction with urine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.18,0:12:37.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because ammonia in\Nour urine Is acid or neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.35,0:12:40.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not alkaline.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.09,0:12:44.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. that's why he needed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.76,0:12:46.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,this ammonia liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.73,0:12:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1S IS pourec IN 0 e wa er\Nin the toilet bowl
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.00,0:12:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then phenolphthalein is poured into\Nthe water in the toilet{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} tan{\r}k.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.47,0:12:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then chemical reaction will occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.14,0:13:00.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And nobody would suspect the\Nstrong smell of ammonia
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.01,0:13:01.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,seeing this dirty restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.14,0:13:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.81,0:13:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But.\NWhere did you get that chemical, sonny?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.02,0:13:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pops asked me to look for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.48,0:13:12.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So when you were saying goodbye\Nat the entrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.12,0:13:14.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I slipped into the room and found it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.06,0:13:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in this room. Mr. Bancho.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.92,0:13:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also found other interesting things
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.66,0:13:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iike phenolphthalein and chloroform.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.33,0:13:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And even a video tape of a Cary movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.60,0:13:29.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A scary movie video tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.94,0:13:32.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! The tape with a ghost woman
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.71,0:13:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,saying. Go home, go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.28,0:13:37.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He-hey
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.01,0:13:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D.Don't tell me that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.81,0:13:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,CC <oo
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.85,0:13:44.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real identity of the ghost my daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.52,0:13:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran saw on the TV screen are the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.72,0:13:52.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,pictures Mr. Bancho\Ntransmitted from the VCR in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.66,0:13:55.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He-he sent the pictures!! How?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.73,0:13:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's simple and easy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.93,0:14:00.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you use\Nthe public antenna of this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.47,0:14:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plug the antenna cord into the output\Nterminal of the VCR in his room
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.38,0:14:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and transmit video pictures to the antenna
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.98,0:14:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the antenna sends the pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.75,0:14:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to the TV in Mr. Otonashfs room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.39,0:14:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.79,0:14:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to do that, you have to be\Nable to set the TV{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}nel
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.66,0:14:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to the appropriate{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}nel to\Nreceive the pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.66,0:14:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you must turn on the TV first,\Nhow do you think
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.70,0:14:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a multi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}nel remote control
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.07,0:14:32.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr @tonashi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.13,0:14:34.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once you enter the name of\Nthe manufacturer of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.70,0:14:36.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,your TV or VCR into the device
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.44,0:14:38.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you can operate any TV or VCR\Nmade by the manufacturer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.61,0:14:39.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So with the multi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}nel remote control,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.81,0:14:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you can operate the TV in\Nsomeone else's room on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.88,0:14:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,without the owner realizing a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.04,0:14:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.88,0:14:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after finding out how the trick worked
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.88,0:14:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it was a piece of cake even for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.52,0:14:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.32,0:14:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This old man was the one who sent\Nthe images to my TV screen a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.95,0:14:57.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I got him to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.49,0:15:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,send the video I just borrowed from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.83,0:15:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used the remote control
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.57,0:15:06.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from outside\Nthe window of Mr. Othonashi's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.97,0:15:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Facing the building under construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.50,0:15:11.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using the wall as a foothold,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.24,0:15:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you could easily send\Nthe signals to his TV set from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.04,0:15:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't even need to watch\Nthe TV screen since
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.08,0:15:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the video was played repeatedly
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.71,0:15:22.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All you had to do was listen to the\Nsound from the TV and set the{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}nel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.65,0:15:25.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And while the sun was still up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.72,0:15:28.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You poured the chloroform\Nonto the windowsill
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.06,0:15:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so that all of us who were in the room\Nwould fall asleep
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.26,0:15:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought you could make
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.20,0:15:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,one of us who suddenly fainted\Nand got up in the dark room, still
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.03,0:15:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,hazy in the head see an eerie illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.67,0:15:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.37,0:15:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.58,0:15:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-but, that was for real. wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.44,0:15:54.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean the figure of a person\Nthat has been looking this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.45,0:15:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. that's not a figure of a person at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.05,0:15:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.69,0:16:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go over and look closer,\Nyou'll see what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.99,0:16:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This..this is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.70,0:16:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moths gathered in large numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.70,0:16:13.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or, to put it more precisely
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.13,0:16:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's an aggregate of male moths.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.24,0:16:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He coated the screen in a human shape\Nwith female moth pheromone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.04,0:16:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that is also used as an insecticide,\Nand stuck eyes and a mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.14,0:16:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,made from black paper on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.51,0:16:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The male moths that were attracted to\Nthe scent of the pheromone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.88,0:16:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,clustered on it to make it\NIook like a human shadow was
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.42,0:16:31.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iooking inside through the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.72,0:16:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, moths kept approaching\Nmy arm several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.03,0:16:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I almost fell from the window\Nwhere I saw the figure for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.63,0:16:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found myself grabbing the screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.77,0:16:52.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and got the pheromone on my arm,\Nwhich attracted moths to me
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.37,0:16:53.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So. that is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.88,0:16:56.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I simply removed the screen\Non the second floor and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.21,0:16:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,placed it by window on the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.98,0:16:59.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.38,0:17:01.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.42,0:17:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why the figure\Nstarted on its own is disappearing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.22,0:17:08.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because Mr. Bansho's black light that\Nwas activated by a timer
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.22,0:17:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was emitted from the window\Nof his room diagonally below.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moths are more prone to be attracted by
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.10,0:17:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ultraviolet light emitted by the\Nblack lights, than the pheromone
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.77,0:17:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the trick would be disclosed\Nif even one moth remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.31,0:17:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why Mr. Bancho hurried across\Nto the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.31,0:17:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as soon as the moths\Nbegan to fly out. then
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.51,0:17:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,opened the window and screen together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.28,0:17:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The force of the impact knocked\Nthe moths off the screen completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.72,0:17:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bancho, you pretended not to notice\Nthe moths even
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.66,0:17:47.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when you got close to the window. right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.33,0:17:52.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because you intentionally caused\Nthis uproar over the ghost
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.23,0:17:56.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But. I still don't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.37,0:18:01.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the chemicals besides the\Nchloroform can be gotten easily. but why
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.84,0:18:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:06.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bancho could've easily made\Nthe video himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.15,0:18:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,by using his scary figures and his falsetto
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.55,0:18:13.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd he go through the trouble\Nof making up a ghost story?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.12,0:18:17.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He attempted to scare us,\NMr. Otonashi's guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.33,0:18:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To get Mr. Otonashi who refused to move\Nto decide to do after all this ghost scare.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.10,0:18:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps. in order to cover up\Nthe crime four years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.97,0:18:31.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crime four years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.41,0:18:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the murder of the the woman\Nburned to death in the park?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.74,0:18:40.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You say you saw the death candle\Nin that building under construction?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.85,0:18:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.05,0:18:47.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was drifting in the air wasn't\Nthe death candle, but a lit cigarette.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.02,0:18:51.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was glowing bluish white
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.73,0:18:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was the light of portable TV that was\Nsecretly being watched.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.26,0:19:00.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!? Don't tell me there's someone\Nin that building?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.87,0:19:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, taking advantage of the fact\Nthe building is still under construction,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.74,0:19:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he's been living in hiding there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.64,0:19:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He is one of the two murderers who was
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.91,0:19:16.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,witnessed four years ago.\NThat has a scar across his cheek!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.29,0:19:21.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps,\NMr. Bancho is one of the two murderers,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.49,0:19:23.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,whose face wasn't witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.79,0:19:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the light of the cigarette\Nwas witnessed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.23,0:19:31.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the fact that somebody\NIived here was about to be disclosed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.10,0:19:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you fabricated and\Naccelerated the plot about the ghost girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.10,0:19:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you-chased the.residents of the condo\Noutione after the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.34,0:19:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because they could look\Ninside the building from their room!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.91,0:19:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did this all to keep your accomplice\Nrom going out into the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.61,0:19:48.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because if so, that accomplice would\Nturn out to be decisive evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.82,0:19:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason that you're living here
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.59,0:19:55.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,IS to bring the guy with the scar across\Nhis cheek, his food and drinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.32,0:19:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because his scar will give him away.
